---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const pageTitle = `Events | ${SITE_TITLE}`;
const pageDescription = 'Upcoming Stride City Run Club events, race meetups, and team outings.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />

		<main>
			<section class="events-hero">
				<div class="container">
					<p class="eyebrow">Upcoming Events</p>
					<h1>Run with Stride City</h1>
					<p class="lede">
						From weekly miles to race-day meetups, this is where we share the events Stride City Run Club is showing up for together.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="events-list">
				<div class="container">
					<article class="event-card event-article">
						<div class="event-card-header">
							<p class="event-kicker">Team Event</p>
							<h2>Run the South with Stride City Run Club</h2>
						</div>

						<p>
							Stride City Run Club is putting together a team for <strong>Run the South Half Marathon, 10K &amp; 5K</strong>, one of Charlotte's summer race events at <strong>McAlpine Creek Park</strong>. Known as <strong>"The Hottest Half,"</strong> the race includes multiple distance options across a two-day format, including a Friday evening 5K and Saturday morning 10K and Half Marathon.
						</p>

						<p>
							The event takes place at <strong>McAlpine Creek Park, 8711 Monroe Rd, Charlotte, NC 28212</strong>. Current event details list the <strong>5K for Friday, June 19, 2026 at 6:15 PM</strong>, followed by the <strong>Half Marathon on Saturday, June 20, 2026 at 7:00 AM</strong> and the <strong>10K on Saturday, June 20, 2026 at 7:30 AM</strong>.
						</p>

						<div class="event-details" aria-label="Run the South event details">
							<div>
								<span>5K</span>
								<strong>Friday, June 19, 2026 at 6:15 PM</strong>
							</div>
							<div>
								<span>Half Marathon</span>
								<strong>Saturday, June 20, 2026 at 7:00 AM</strong>
							</div>
							<div>
								<span>10K</span>
								<strong>Saturday, June 20, 2026 at 7:30 AM</strong>
							</div>
							<div>
								<span>Location</span>
								<strong>McAlpine Creek Park, 8711 Monroe Rd, Charlotte, NC 28212</strong>
							</div>
							<div>
								<span>Club plan</span>
								<strong>Stride City team meetup</strong>
							</div>
							<div>
								<span>Race options</span>
								<strong>5K, 10K, Half Marathon, and challenge options</strong>
							</div>
						</div>

						<p>
							Run the South is a great fit for Stride City because the course is described as fast and flat, with a route through mostly shaded greenways and wide open gravel paths. Whether you are chasing a PR, trying a new distance, or just looking for a fun race-day atmosphere with familiar faces, this is a strong summer goal race for the club.
						</p>

						<p>
							All distances include race swag such as running sunglasses, a shirt option, and a custom finisher medal. The race also offers virtual options for runners who want to participate on their own schedule.
						</p>

						<h3>Join the Stride City team</h3>
						<p>
							Stride City Run Club will have a team at Run the South, and we would love for you to join us. Register for the distance that works best for you, then look for the Stride City Run Club team option when signing up.
						</p>

						<h3>Race options</h3>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>5K</strong> — Friday, June 19 at 6:15 PM</li>
							<li><strong>10K</strong> — Saturday, June 20 at 7:30 AM</li>
							<li><strong>Half Marathon</strong> — Saturday, June 20 at 7:00 AM</li>
							<li><strong>Challenge options</strong> — Run the Friday 5K, then come back Saturday for the 10K or Half Marathon</li>
						</ul>

						<h3>What to expect from Stride City</h3>
						<p>
							As race day gets closer, we will share meetup details, team timing, and any packet pickup or pre-race plans. Wear your Stride City gear if you have it, bring water, and plan for summer heat. All paces are welcome. Come to race, run, walk, cheer, or support the team.
						</p>

						<p>
							Run the South is a chance to show up together, celebrate the progress we have made on Wednesday nights, and bring that same Stride City energy to the starting line.
						</p>
					</article>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>

		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.events-hero {
		padding: 5em 1.5em 4em;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.92), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.72));
		color: #fff;
	}

	.events-hero h1 {
		margin: 0 0 0.35em;
		font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4rem);
		line-height: 1;
		color: #fff;
	}

	.eyebrow,
	.event-kicker {
		margin: 0 0 0.5em;
		color: var(--accent);
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.12em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
	}

	.lede {
		max-width: 680px;
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.82);
	}

	.events-list {
		padding: 4em 1.5em;
		background: #fff;
	}

	.event-card {
		padding: clamp(1.5em, 4vw, 2.5em);
		border: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
		border-radius: 18px;
		box-shadow: 0 14px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
	}

	.event-article {
		max-width: 860px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.event-card-header {
		margin-bottom: 1em;
	}

	.event-card h2 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
		line-height: 1.05;
	}

	.event-card p,
	.event-card li {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}

	.event-details {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1em;
		margin: 2em 0;
	}

	.event-details div {
		padding: 1em;
		border-radius: 14px;
		background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
	}

	.event-details span {
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: 0.3em;
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
	}

	.event-details strong {
		display: block;
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}

	.event-card h3 {
		margin-top: 1.75em;
		font-size: 1.35rem;
	}

	.event-card ul {
		margin: 0;
		padding-left: 1.2em;
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.event-details {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
